Premier League club Brentford has sent a good luck message to Frank Onyeka as the Super Eagles prepare to take on the Black Stars of Ghana on Tuesday. Both teams will lock horns in the second leg of the 2022 World Cup qualifying playoffs inside the MKO Abiola stadium in Abuja. Aside Onyeka, Brentford also sent their best wishes to their striker Yoane Wissa who is expected to feature for DR Congo against Morocco.   Women T20I: Nigeria claims 41-run victory over Sierra Leone     Ronaldo admits tough test  against North Macedonia     Salah leads Egypt ‘ World Cup war’ against  Senegal   DR Congo were forced to a 1-1 draw by the Atlas Lions in the reverse fixture last Friday. Onyeka helped the Eagles hold the Black Stars to a goalless draw four days ago when both rivals clashed in Kumasi. And ahead of the playoffs, Brentford wrote on their Twitter handle: ”The decisive night in @CAF_Online #WCQ2022 tonight. “Good luck, lads.”